dcterms:description: A large internal training set of roughly 2 million 2D-aligned images of around 200K individuals, with at least 3 images per individual, used for training the Exemplar GANs.
dcterms:title: Internal benchmark

dcterms:description: A publicly-available benchmark dataset for eye in-painting, developed from high-quality images of celebrities scraped from the web, containing around 17K individual identities and a total of 100K images.
dcterms:title: Eye in-painting benchmark

dcterms:description: A publicly-available benchmark dataset for face recognition, containing a large number of unique identities, but with limitations in terms of image quality and pose.
dcterms:title: Celeb-ID

dcterms:creator: A. Nech
I. Kemelmacher-Shlizerman
dcterms:description: A dataset designed for face recognition tasks, providing a level playing field for evaluating algorithms on a million scale.
dcterms:title: MegaFace

dcterms:description: A publicly-available benchmark dataset for evaluating generative models, specifically for in-painting tasks.
dcterms:title: Exemplar GANs
